reviews: This is a gem of a hotel with the nucest staff of any hotel I have ever stayed at. Excellent breakfast at a low price. Great air conditioning. Nice amenities. Excellent location, very close to Eiffel Tower and L’Ecole Militaire Metro.

Our family thoroughly enjoyed our stay at this lovely hotel near Rue Clerc and the Eiffel Tower. Small and clean with wonderful staff. We didn’t try the breakfast but it looked good. Lots of good restaurants near by. Beautiful neighborhood.

This hotel I would rate 10 out of 10. You will love everything about it, staff, amenities,location, close to great restaurants on rue Cler, close to Metro, but walking distance from Musee dOrsay, Eiffel Tower , etc.

My friend and I have just returned to Manchester from 2 days in Paris and stayed at this hotel.
We really enjoyed it. We found the room really quiet, clean and bright and we were able to make a cup of tea and coffee in our room in the morning, which is always a big plus.
The staff were so friendly and helpful and the location was great!
Carla & Lilly

Excellent place, friendly staff, very clean. Our expectations were exceeded at this beautiful, centrally located gem! The 70’s vibe mixed with modern flare made our Paris experience that much better! Highly recommend to all

I loved staying at this hotel. It is in a very safe area, a short walk from the Eiffel Tower park. There were grocery stores and restaurants nearby, as well as an entrance to the metro. The staff were extremely kind, even giving me a map of Paris as well as some suggestions. I loved the room itself, it was comfortable, and the design was so convenient and cool. The wifi was also amazing. 10/10 would recommend this place!!

Absolutely lovely hotel with a beautiful view and perfect location, only a 5 minute walk from the Eiffel Tower. Extremely friendly staff both day and night. Not a bad word to say. 100% recommend and will stay again!

The hotel was in a great location and the staff were very helpful. We arrived on Sunday night and found a great bistro nearby. From our room we had a spectacular view of the Eiffel Tower. What more could you ask?

Hotel Eiffel Turenne is a nice little hidden gem. It is affordable and accommodates families. We had two connecting rooms. Rooms are small as is expected in Europe but was comfortable and clean. Wifi and breakfast were nice amenities. It is in a great location. We walked to the Eiffel Tower every night. The metro/bus station is less than a block away. There are several cafes within 2-3 minutes. A grocery store is only a block away. In all, very comfortable, affordable and convenient to seeing Paris!

Amazing location, quiet, clean, comfortable, affordable! Room is small, but that's not a problem for a few nights. Totally worth the price. Booked last-minute (first time to Paris) and this hotel exceeded expectations!

Great location 5 minutes walk from the Eiffel Tower and 1 minute from the metro station. Modern and clean room. Bruno's service was exceptional, he helped us with information in a clear and polite way.
Definitely a place to come back

The location is really nice. It is easy to find this place and it has good connection with the most important tourist routes. Room was very clean and cozy. View was ok. Breakfast very good. Everything worked perfectly.

Would thoroughly recommend this hotel. Stayed with my husband for three nights. Greeted by a lovely gentleman on reception on our first night, friendly and helpful. All the staff we met were the same.
Excellent location, super comfy bed and lovely warm shower.

Very well situated, center and quiet, very convenient, close to many wonderful sites, transport and shops.
The guys at the reception are very smart, kind and helpfuls.
I highly recommend the hotel and would be happy to return

Hotel Eiffel Turenne was a 100% positive experience for my last stay in Paris, great and helpful staff, clean, functional and pleasing rooms, good breakfast and more. The location has several nice and informal cafés and bars, and is close to the Metro if you need to get around. I will definitely be back.
Highly recommended.

The room was larger than expected, arranged efficiently and very clean. The breakfast was convenient and very good. The location was central for many sites that we visited when walking and the metro was very close.

Very very rude front desk man. Doesn’t like anyone including guests or anyone guests invite over to sit in the lobby. He will yell at you if you sit down. Doesn’t like anyone to talk either. He will say you are too loud. Not welcoming at all. Such a temper for no reason. People are coming to vacation and he should understand that. Very bad impression of Paris people.

The lock of door is not working, feel so unsecured, the staff can’t fix it and my belongings is stay inside a unlock room for 12 hours… I feel so bad to yr management and won’t recommend any ppl come over

Day before my arrival to Paris my flight was cancelled because of country strike! I already paid for 3 night stay, I contacted hotel about this and sent flight cancellation and hotel refused to refund my money or refund at least half of my payment! They don’t respond to my request any more!

The staff is the best part of the hotel. Perfect location, extremely clean and well maintained. Breakfast is simple, but in my opinion the 13 euros was worth it as they offer bread, eggs, fruits and yogurts. I strongly recommend it.

I felt cozy while I was staying. It seems that staff gave a warm welcome to us. Besides, the staff were very kind and helpful. It was also good to see Youtube channel on TV. It was located near to the station and Eiffel tower. Also you can easily find the local mart and launderette near hotel.

What a surprise it was. The Hotel is excellent, like a boutique type, breakfast is delicious with all types of french pastries, and the staff is super friendly and professional. We will recommend this Hotel to all our friends, super clean, the shower is great, and near a metro station and within walking distance of the tower. Mi regards to the staff all over , all did a great job. We will repeat.

This is such a wonderful hotel in a great location. Very close the metro and walking distance from many restaurants bars and attractions. The room was typically “European small” which wasn’t a big deal to us because the shower and bed were both amazing. The staff is amazingly kind and thoughtful-especially Raphaela. Will definitely stay here again!

Where to start. A perfect stay. I have stayed in Paris several times and this hotel will now be my preferred place to book. The staff are so accommodating, friendly and helpful. We arrived early from Gare Du Nord but it was no problem. Our bags were stored away for us. I even got a text later in the day to say that our bags had been taken up to our room. The loveliest surprise was that the hotel staff upgraded our room to a larger one as we were staying for four nights. Thank you so much guys. Loved the decor. Love the location. Two minutes from Ecole Millitaire Metro stop. Three minutes from Rue Cler with its lovely food shopping. Decent choice of cafes and restaurants that surround the hotel. Best of all I could walk the ten minutes each evening to watch the Eiffel Tower twinkle . Parfait ….Merci Beaucoup Hotel Eiffel Turenne. We will be back for sure. Thoroughly recommend you. 💙❤️🤍

Centrally located, clean, modern, excellent breakfast and very friendly staff. Perfect for a weekend stay + Affordable. I was on my way back from a business trip in Copenhagen and decided vist Paris for the weekend. I am so glad I found this hotel! I was able to easily walk to the Eiffel Tower and Louvre. I will be back for sure. Thumbs up!

amazing place, with amazing people and very helpful. they really care about their gusset. i asked one simple question and they new i was lost of directions. they provided me with a map and spend almost 30 minutes explaining and recommending places to make sure i have good stay in Paris. Amazing!!

I Am happy that I decided to change my hotel from the previous one I booked to Hotel Eiffel Turenne as this hotel was perfect for the 3 nights stay in Paris.
Location was perfect for the holiday in Paris and the staff were very accommodating.
Will surely book this hotel again on my next visit.
A welcome gift was a very sweet gesture since they know that we are celebrating our anniversary.

very kind and thoughtful experience throughout from checking in advance what I would like to the way they looked after my baggage or allowed me to check in a little earlier due to availability. I really liked the team, every member of staff was welcoming, helpful and kind. They had a lot of little touches to make the hotel feel like a home away from home

They have a communal space to relax, do work or take phone calls etc - very good touch as many hotels in Paris are so crammed they dont have this facility.

Only area of improvement is fluffier towels or heated towel racks. Even consider Netflix on TV.

Very friendly and helpful staff. Hotel is just 15 minutes from the Eiffel Tower and many cafe's and restaurants. The front desk gave us wonderful recommendations for where to have lunch and dinner. 24 hour reception. Clean room. Small room but comfortable enough for us and 6 pieces of luggage.

The room was very nice. And the staff very friendly. They helped me with every question.
I will stay in your hotel again. Close to the centre of Paris. A very nice neighbourhood. Not te busy, but not to quiet.

The hotel Eiffel Turenne is close to the Seine and multiple Parisian landmarks making ideal for a weekend trip. The staff is welcoming, professional, multilingual and friendly. The room was very comfortable and clean.

The hotel is well-located, a block from a Metro station, convenient to shops and cafes, and steps from Rue Cler. The Eiffel Tower, Les Invalides, Seine River, and Orsay Museum are within walking distance. The staff is friendly and helpful. A good buffet breakfast (extra charge) is provided in the cozy, nicely decorated lobby/lounge area. The only downside is that the rooms are small, but this is common in European hotels.

We went back to France to visit my husband’s family for a couple weeks and stayed for 2 nights here before heading home. We had 2 adults and 1 kid (2 years old). Baby slept with us but they do have pack n play beds that they can put in the room if you book a room that is big enough to fit one- their website indicates which rooms allow for this. Staff was very welcoming and gave us a nice room that was clean and comfortable. Great location. Close to a metro station, 10 minute walk to Eiffel Tower. Staff called a taxi for us to get to the airport in the morning and it was there very quickly.

Very nice stay. Easy access to the Metro. Lots of restaurants nearby along with fast food and grocery store options. Laundry mat right across the street was a great bonus that we took advantage of. Would stay here again!

Great stay, thanks!

Great location and really friendly and helpful staff. Room a little small but comfortable, good showers and very clean. Would definitely recommend if you are visiting this part of Paris.

Me and my daughter had a great time in this hotel, very good front desk service especially from Bruno, hotel has a great location everything around very close to Eiffel Tower, good breakfast and very clean room I really recommend and for sure will gone stay again.

Good location and good staff but rooms galleries and lift are too small.
The worst thing is they took 220€ deposit without informing in advance at time of booking.
They must mention it at time of booking.

Amazing hotel and great customer service, the hotel is only 13 minutes from the Effiel Tower, and have a lot of restaurants around. The area is very friendly and quiet, the train station is only 5 minute. Is nice place to stay on Paris

We only stayed one night in Paris. The place is ideally located to explore and to have a cosy room to stay. The view on the street-side was also nice, a typical french avenue. Very friendly staff. We really enjoyed our stay and looking forward to come back.

This hotel was a good find after a disappointing one. It is very close to the metro Ecole Militaire, with many buses, shops and restaurants. The room was a little small but very comfortable. It is expected in Paris. The bed was comfortable, and had a great shower. We could also open the window, which became a mini fridge for us LOL. They are also soundproof. All the staff was super pleasant and helpful. Nothing to complain about.

The location is very close to metro and bus. It's about 20 mins walking distance to Eiffel Tower. Many good restaurants nearby. Staff is super friendly. My room faces to the road and on 3rd floor so I can hear the noise but it's not too bad and kind of acceptable. The room is very small but clean and comfort. Electric kettle is very helpful in such chill days.

Location is very good. Staffs were friendly and the room was clean. The day receiption gave us a warm complimentary coffee from the house, which I find a very pleasant gesture. Overall it was a nice and lovely experience for me.

Beautiful place
Excellent service
Great location
Clean
Nice bed
Great restaurants
Art Basel Fair few minuts away
Sunny
High ceiling
Pleasant
Charming
Paris experience
Wondeful stuff at front desk
I will be back

Very nice and clean hotel close to Eiffel Tower
Nice zone in Paris, nice hotel, small but very nice room, very clean bathroom, very nice bed and bed furniture. If you need to stay a couple of days in Paris, this is a very good choice

Had a great time staying here for a romantic getaway to France. Located close enough to all without feeling like you are being swarmed with crowds. Would highly recommend the picnic basket offered for a romantic picnic under the Eiffel Tower.

Very close to shopping, dining, cafes, bakery, and 15 minutes to the Eiffel Tower. Walking distance to everything. Rooms are not that big, but the windows open to get air in. Breakfast buffet was nice.

Great little hotel, with tiny rooms as one finds in Paris, with barely enough room to get around the bed, and closet basically a bar to hang things and shelf in the room, so sort of like sleeping in your closet. On the plus side: air conditioning, private bathroom, on site breakfast, walking distance to metro. Incredibly friendly staff, they helped us book museum pass, Eiffel tour, river cruise, when the booking options for Paris activities can be confusing and overwhelming.

Excellent location, room so clean, but what it really makes it special is the people working there, they always in a good mood and willing to help us.

Is just a few steps to the underground and you can easily walk to the eiffel tower and the invalides park, also there are a lot of nice restaurants in the street and supermarket.

The attendants at the front desk were very cordial and helpful.
The downside was the size of the room, it was so narrow and small. The hotel was convenient to places to visit. There were nice places to eat near the hotel

Rooms are small, nut the services, the good people, and the location are the best. You will not regret. Humberto, is an beautiful person. Help us a lot. The hotel are in a good location from Tower Effeil and the metro.

I have traveled to Paris numerous times and this hotel is by far one of the best!! The location is amazing,the rooms are wonderful but most importantly the staff is so kind, helpful and caring. Thank you to Humberto, Aget
Noemi and Karim for making my stay so comfortable and memorable! Will definitely be back!

Really good value, very clean and modern rooms with excellent service within 10 minutes walk of the Eiffel Tower and 2 minutes of metro. We had the interconnecting rooms which were perfect for a family of 4. Breakfast is also very good and staff very helpful.

Charming people, clean, central, good prices, nice food. Near to eiffel tower, to train station, a laundry an so far. I recommend this place to stay in Paris, people is very kind and safety, no problems at all in my stay.

This hotel was wonderful for our stay in Paris! It is modern and up to date. The location is fantastic with a quick walk to the Eiffel Tower. The metro station is right around the corner to get you everywhere you need in the city. We walked everywhere and loved the location. The hotel staff are extremely helpful and the rooms are clean and cool - something important to us. The rooms are small but that is what you are going to get anywhere in Paris for the price point. We were still able to fit a big travel backpack and one large suitcase comfortably in our room. Highly recommend this stay and we will be back!

Everyone was very friendly and helpful and made our stay special. The hotel had easy access to the metro, and many interesting sites and cafes were within walking distance. We would definitely stay there again!

The location of the hotel is outstanding! 20 minutes walking distance from the Eiffel Tower. Cafes, grocery stores, bakeries, ATM you name it and it’s in 5-10 minutes walking distance. I had booked a single occupancy room and was shocked when I checked in. The room was like a matchbox so tiny that I could barely keep my luggage and move around. Also the lift was not working for the first two days though the staff helped with carrying my luggage but it was inconvenient.

The AC was great and there was hot shower which made up for the inconvenience. Would like to make a special mention of Naomi who was super helpful & very sweet. Helped me with booking my cab at the last minute and was very warm. All in all my stay was comfortable.

Located close to the Eiffel Tower as the name implies. Close to metro. Decent hotel with well appointed rooms and an excellent bathroom (although limited toiletries). Comfortable bed, good TV with wide selection of channels from different countries. Downside - very expensive for what it was. Maybe it was a busy week in Paris, but I think about half the price would have been fair.

The staff were accommodating and helpful. I booked through a travel agent. When I arrived they saw my reservation but did not have an actual room reserved. I originally reserved for room facing the street. The staff however was very helpful and was able to book me a room quickly and I did not have to wait that long to be assigned a room. So, I was able to quickly check-in and go about my day to enjoy Paris. I was given a room that was not facing the street however but it was fine with me as I was out almost the whole day. The room was small but clean. The breakfast area was cozy.

I was on business travel, but it is one of the best hotels I stayed in—a very cozy elegant, and comfortable room. no noise a completely relaxed Clean, nice personnel, nice breakfast buffet ..

I recommended it a lot!

The staff was very firendly. They let us to check in earlier. However, the rooms seems like does not have sound isolation at all. We literally heard every single minor sound from the neighbour rooms..

We moved to Hotel Eiffel Turenne because the previous hotel we were staying in, wasn't what we expected. Hotel Eiffel Turenne saved our trip! As soon as we walked in, we felt welcomed. The room had a great view and it was very clean. Breakfast was wonderful and the staff very helpful and friendly! Hotel Eiffel Turenne truly saved us from having a bad experience in Paris. We definitely recommend this hotel!

The cutest little hotel and a great location, especially if you’re looking for something less touristy. All of the front desk staff were kind and incredibly helpful. The rooms and bathrooms are a little small, but they were modern, clean, and efficient. We were able to walk to the Eiffel Tower in less than 10 minutes and there is a metro station right around the corner. I would definitely stay here again!

We had a great stay at this boutique hotel. We wanted to be out of the touristy areas and this was perfect. Walking distance to Eiffel Tower and other destinations and has a subway station on the street over. Great restaurants, friendly staff, sparkling clean. Breakfast offered was good. Rooms are smaller side but we expected that. It was a wonderful stay.

Our return stay was just as good as our first. Perfect location in the comfortable Rue Cler neighborhood with good restaurants and easy transportation to the rest of the city. The rooms modern and clean as is the bathroom and bathroom fixtures. Staff is super-helpful. The room is small, even by French standards, but you don’t come to Paris to stay in your room.

We went to Paris for a quick few days. This was a great hotel for our budget. So helpful during our stay. Highly recommend to those looking to see the sights - most were walkable. Staff provided recommendations and assistance before we arrived and during our stay. Very friendly!

Within walking distance of the Eiffel Tower and the subway. There’s a bus stop right in front of the hotel as well as easy access to taxis. Lots of Cafes and souvenir stores nearby. Helpful and courteous staff.

We had a lovely stay at Hotel Eiffel Turenne, the hotel has a perfect location only 500mt from the Eiffel Tower.
The staff was great, the rooms a bit small but very nice and clean.
Breakfast was good and generous.

Clean room, enjoyable stay. We did not take breakfast here, because of allergies and in Paris there are lots off other options, so I can not comment on the breakfast. But everything in our room was more than ok.

I absolutely loved this hotel. The room was very comfortable and quiet, and I loved that I could open all the windows. The bathroom was great and it had a towel warmer! The staff was super friendly and they all spoke English very well. The location is also great. If I visit Paris again, I will definitely stay there again.

We were very kindly welcomed by Maria who spoke good English. The place was clean and in tune with what we expected. The bed was very small and the mattrasses very hard. We didn’t sleep that well. That’s all

Nice and comfortable, central position near to the metro e bus station, small room and clean.. Kindness by the property in every moment. Good international breakfast. Suggested for some days in Paris.

Friendly and helpful staff.
Perfect location, just a 13 minute walk from the Eiffel Tower.
Very clean room and bathroom. We got a free upgrade.
We did not eat the hotel breakfast as there was not much variety and we prefered to eat in a cafe.
Metro, bus many cafes, restuarants and supermarket very close by.

Overall a perfect location close to everything. The ladies at the front desk were wonderful. The rooms are small but have everything you need. There were some ants in the room but it wasn’t terrible. Breakfast was a little repetitive but nice to have the option. Overall fantastic stay!

Great location. Friendly and helpful staff. 5 minute walk to Eiffel Tower. Next to taxi queue and laundromat. Clean and comfortable. Lovely breakfast. Great coffee. I would book there again next time.

We booked this on a “last minute” rate of $400 for the weekend, total for both nights. Much more reasonable than other hotels in the area. It’s a wonderful location, right around the corner from the Rue Cler neighborhood and 3/4 of mile from Eiffel Tower. Clean rooms, friendly and helpful staff and wonderful breakfast for €13. Double pane windows in our fourth floor room kept it mostly quiet at night. Would definitely stay there again. You can’t beat the location.

The location is great. About a 10 minute walk to the tower. Grocery/convenience store a block away. ATM/bank across the street Rx/pharmacy one block away. And many eateries nearby. We ate breakfast each morning in the hotel because it was delicious and easy. The room is small but functional and very clean. The front desk staff was super helpful with all our needs. Whether it be dropping out bags before our room was ready, calling and arranging transportation to and from the airport or giving us plates and silverware for our evening snacks we brought in. I would recommend! About 40 minutes from CDG airport in the 7th arrondissement

This was such a cute hotel! Our room was little, but very functional! It had everything we needed. The best part was the window that opened and had an iron rail with a view of the street. Bathroom was little also, but it was perfect. We loved staying here!

Great location, close to the Eiffel Tower about a 5/10 minute walk, great view from the hotel too. Really clean, comfy bed and staff were lovely. Definitely will be staying again and really recommend it to anyone!

One if the best hotels that I rest in
I strongly recommend it
Breakfast was composed by a very huge buffet with all the specialities of France
The enturage is very kind
The room was very clean and tidy

I am so grateful I found this lovely little boutique hotel, it was the perfect location to have an adventure and sightseeing on foot. Very short walk to the Eiffel tower I’m not too far to the louvre. Great restaurants and grocery stores right close. And the staff was very kind and helpful for whatever I needed. The room was small but comfortable, lovely bed, Great shower, great towels, and a tea kettle in the room. The windows open so you can let some fresh air in. The best part was their breakfast, which is Buffet style and delicious. Make sure to have a cappuccino, they added just a little bit of chocolate which seems to be a normal thing in Paris, and is not a bad thing, my soul was happy with every sip. Big thank you to the girls at the front desk, your employers are lucky to have you! Great service! I highly recommend this hotel especially for a first timers, solo travelers, or a couple on a romantic getaway.

Hotel is very good for a 3 star. We found it very clean, in a perfect location (safe and accessible), with great staff. The rooms are not big... but it is ok for couple, for short stays. I definitely recommend.

Very good location between the Eiffel Tower and the Louvre Museum, and the Hotel was very clean and practical. Good breakfast. Very quite and confortable. .The people from the Hotel was very friendly.

Extremely Clean, Tidy, and comfortable.
Staff are Children Friendly and go out of their way to assist with anything needed 24/7.
Excellent Location.
The lack of space is the fact of almost all hotels in Paris, especially in the town centre

every one was very helpful and kind. really enjoyed my stay. I highly recommend this hotel. would definitely stay again in future. my 18 month son loved the staff and hotel as well. The breakfast option was not much but was of good quality and tasty.❤❤

Most amazing stay at this hotel! We were lucky enough to get a room upgrade and stayed in 603 which was very spacious and had a view of the Eiffel Tower. Our room was cleaned each day for our 3 nights and it was always quiet in the room. Hotel is right beside a metro station and a short 15/20 min walk to the Eiffel tower. I'd recommend having the hotel breakfast as the price was much cheaper than any of the local cafes. It was buffet style and there was a great choice of cooked/ continental items. Try avoid using the taxi rank taxis, they charge a fortune. Definitely use Uber as this was much cheaper, or the Metros. There is plenty cafes/ restaurants/ bars within close proximity. Would love to come back here one day!

I had an awesome stay at Eiffel Taurenne, the staff was really friendly, the location it's perfect and the room was really good for a two days stay. I was travelling alone and I felt really confortable staying in this hotel, I will definitely come back.

This hotel is perfect for a business trip oder short-term stay in Paris. Single-Rooms are not spacious, but very clean and if you would like to enjoy more space, you can use a common area, which is very cozy. The breakfast is very good as well, very kind staff. Moreover the hotel is perfectly located. All in all: Highly recommended.

The location of the hotel is great, in walking distance to the Eiffel Tower and right next to a metro station. The service is great, with clean, quality rooms and a delicious breakfast. The staff is friendly and helpful.

This property is very close to the Invalides and Eiffel Tower. We stayed here for 6 days and nights, and enjoyed the location and amenities. Definitely worth considering for future travel as a very good value.

It was the best hotell. I loved the room, it was close to everything in Paris. The staff was so nice and helpfull. I Will definitiv come back. The room was Also very clean. And the bathroom was nice too. I really recommend it

The staff it super friendly, nice and always available to help you. Located in the heart of Paris : 5 min walk to the nearest metro, surrounded by many restaurants, a pharmacy also 15 min walk to the Eiffel Tower.
The room is very well kept, clean, I think it’s small, but it’s a common thing in Paris. It offers all you need for a short stay.
Breakfast is delicious and the common areas are very well decorated . I felt safe on this hotel (covid).
Next time I go to Paris, I’ll definitely stay here . ❤️

Very good hotel, clean and with good breakfast with a lot of choices. Excelent location in the city centre. Specialized staff. We are sure that we will choose another time again for our trip to Paris. Merci!

A very cozy hotel, elegant room, spotless clean, and perfect location within walking distance to landmarks and restaurants. My one comment is slightly uncomfortable pillows but everything else was perfect.

The hotel room was small (as expected in Paris), but very cozy and clean. I loved the shower fountain head and that apart from the usual amenities (shower gel, shampoo, etc.), the hotel also provided teabags and kettle, a small sewing kit for on the go and other useful stuff.

The only thing that annoyed me was that when you use the hair-dryer, you continually have to press down with your hand, giving you a cramp after five minutes. I think the hotel could work out another solution for it to stop working when you stop using it.

The hotel staff was very nice and accommodating, the lobby was also decorated festively.

The place was cute. But rooms were not too clean. Very dusty and housekeeping was bare minimum. We were not able to use the tv and no one knew how to adjust or fix it. They Weren’t very helpful when we asked questions or suggestions. Their breakfast and coffee service however was excellent

Clean charming room with super helpful staff. Very close to a Metro station, supermarket, chemist and news stand. You can walk to the Eiffel Tower in 10-15 minutes. Room was very clean.
Ticks all the boxes.

Hotel staff, and I mean every single one, were very kind. The rooms were very clean, did not question hygiene at any point (goes for Hotel restrooms and lobby as well). The location was perfect, walking distance from the Eiffel Tower and 3 stops away from the famous shopping streets. The neighborhood has its own loveliness and was very safe. 100/10 recommend this place to anyone considering staying in Paris.

Super friendly and helpful staff as well as located in a great location with several restaurants and convenient stores around. It is also approximately 10-15 minutes from the Eiffel Tower. The room was a bit small, but it was really well kept and is probably normal for a hotel in Paris.

The hotel was clean and the staff was very helpfull and polite But your standart room was very narrow. The location was good I wish to stay in your hotel in the furure with my family but with such narrow rooms with this price level I may not be chosing yor hotel

Hotel is pretty, location is very key for moving around the city, super close to the Eiffel Tower and waking distance from Metro station and super secure area. I was traveling on my own and felt so secure. People working at the hotel have the ideal customer service mindset, Humberto at reception helped me a lot to suggest places to visit and they were all so helpful. Definitely a great option to stay at Paris and a perfect relationship cost-benefit
